Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Put the @onion marmalade{30%g} into a #bowl{} and use a spoon to break it up.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily 
slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on 
medium-high heat. Season the @British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @?pepper{}.

Once hot, add the pork steaks. Cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Reduce the heat to medium, then fry for an additional ~{4-6%minutes}, turning every 
couple of mins.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Once the chicken has rested, transfer to a #baking tray{}.

Spread the onion marmalade onto the steaks. Top with the grated cheese, pressing it 
down with the back of a spoon.

When hot, grill until the cheese is golden and bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Allow to 
rest for ~{2%minutes} before serving.

While the chicken is grilling, pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high 
heat (no need to clean). Add a drizzle of oil if needed.

Once hot, add the green beans and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until 
starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, then turn the heat down to 
medium and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of @water{splash} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. 
Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat. 
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the 
pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{splash} (if you have any) and 
mash until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

When everything's ready, serve the chicken with the mash, garlicky beans and a dollop 
of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside.

Enjoy!